id: pm-dlfq
title: Fix GitHub #98 dependency --dep type parsing
description: "GitHub issue #98 reports that pm update --dep \"type=blocked-by,id=...\" stores the whole key/value string as the dependency id instead of parsing it as structured dependency metadata. Duplicate check: pm search for dependency type/id parsing, custom field setter, and service renderer override found no open direct duplicate before creating this item."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",dependencies,github-issue
created_at: "2026-06-02T15:51:49.839Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-02T16:05:10.950Z"
author: codex-gpt5
parent: pm-mpbb
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-02T15:54:49.273Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: create/update dependency parsers now recognize type as structured dependency metadata, normalize type=blocked-by to blocked_by, and support the same alias in --dep-remove selectors. Focused regression passed: 3 files, 198 tests."
  "2026-06-02T15:59:26.567Z",codex-gpt5,"Static gate follow-up: moved the CLI regression into tests/integration/dependency-alias.integration.spec.ts so tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts stays below the file-length threshold."
  "2026-06-02T16:05:10.950Z",codex-gpt5,"Final verification evidence: node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode best-effort passed on the final tree after dependency updates and the focused integration-file split. Coverage gate reported 136 files, 2096 tests, 100% coverage."
